modules.description: Injects a binary blob from a URL as a string during compilation by executing an HTTP GET request. Processes HTTP 301 redirects and emits a warning for potential security risks. Enables embedding of compressed or arbitrary data directly into OCaml code without lexical constraints.

Provides functions to parse and generate code for handling HTTP request parameters and body data, including extracting attribute values from OCaml syntax trees. Works with Parsetree expressions, type declarations, and location information to process GET, POST, and JSON-based data. Used to automatically derive serialization and deserialization logic for web framework endpoints.
